ent and thus do not require reits to pay state income tax shareholders pay taxes on dividends received and on any capital gains a reit cannot pass any tax losses through to its investors for more information visit national association of real estate investment trusts nareit how can i get other questions answered please submit your question using the information request form corporate profile  colony starwood homes orlando florida investors ir menu corporate profile corporate governance officers  trustees governance documents reporting violations of applicable laws committee composition press releases sec filings quarterly results annual reports stock and dividend information dividends dividend income tax treatment form   organizational actions historic prices analyst coverage company presentations frequently asked questions investor resources contact us email notification site map search entire ir site press releases only filings only corporate profile webcast second quarter  earnings conference call thursday august th   am et domestic  international  on january   starwood waypoint residential trust completed its merger with colony american homes inc in connection with the merger the name of the company was changed to colony starwood homes on january   the company’s common shares began trading under the ticker symbol sfr on the new york stock exchange colony starwood homes acquires renovates leases maintains and manages single family homes colony starwood homes is reinventing renting™ by building a leading nationally recognized brand that is based on a foundation of respect for its residents and the communities in which it operates news releases  colony starwood homes to release second quarter  financial results press release   pm et scottsdale arizbusiness wire colony starwood homes nysesfr the “company” a leading singlefamily rental real estate investment trust “reit” will release its second q  more  colony starwood homes to change name to starwood waypoint homes 